imdb.plot outline: The Six-Episode Series On the Camino de Santiago, produced by La Nube Studio for National Geographic Channels International, premiere on May 2009. Hosted by the Galician musician Xoel López, ex-leader of the Spanish pop group Deluxe, and guided only by the Codex Calixtinus, an ancient manuscript book written in the 12th century, we will travel from Holland, through Belgium and France and, crossing the Pyrenees towards Santiago de Compostela in Spain. The Series, filmed originally in English, French and Spanish, was aired on National Geographic Channels International from May 2009; it was also aired in Spanish speaking territories, with a total of 161 countries and 27 different languages.
